results.name: Decimal expansion of 32*Pi^4/945.
comment: More generally, the ordinary generation function for the volume of the n-dimensional unit sphere is exp(Pi*x^2)*(erf(sqrt(Pi)*x) + 1) = 1 + 2*x + Pi*x^2 + (4*Pi/3)*x^3 + (Pi^2/2)*x^4 + ...
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Ilya Gutkovskiy, Volume of the n-dimensional unit sphere
xref: Cf. similar sequences of the volume of the n-dimensional unit sphere: A000796 (n = 2), 10*A019699 (n = 3), A102753 (n = 4), A164103 (n = 5), A164105 (n = 6), A164106 (n = 7), A164108 (n = 8).
results.author: _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Aug 16 2016
